# Logging Rules

## General Logging Principles

- Use appropriate logging levels for different types of information
- Include context and relevant details in log messages
- Use consistent log message formatting across all file types
- Configure appropriate log retention policies

## Python Logging

- Use the Python logging module for logging
- Use log levels: debug, info, warn, error
- Set a log retention policy of 7 days
- Configure logging in the application's main module

## Configuration File Logging

- Use consistent comment formatting for logging important events
- Include timestamps or version information in config files
- Log configuration changes and their impact
- Use descriptive names for configuration sections

## G-code and Macro Logging

- Include informative comments explaining complex operations
- Log parameter values and their effects
- Use consistent comment formatting for debugging
- Document any conditional logic or error handling

## Log Message Format

- Use clear, descriptive language
- Include relevant context (file, function, parameters)
- Use consistent capitalization and punctuation
- Avoid overly verbose or cryptic messages
